## Purpose

Guide implementation of the NestJS backend (`@draft-io/backend`): HTTP APIs, use cases, domain logic, and persistence. Controllers are thin adapters; all business rules live in domain entities and use cases.

## Required Behavior

### API Conventions

- Global prefix: `api/v1` (set in `main.ts`).
- All successful responses wrap data in `{ data: T }` using `ApiResponse<T>` from `@draft-io/shared-types`.
- Use appropriate HTTP verbs: `POST` create (201), `GET` read, `PATCH` partial update, `DELETE` remove.
- DTOs use `class-validator` decorators; global `ValidationPipe` enforces `whitelist`, `forbidNonWhitelisted`, `transform`.

### Controllers

- One controller per aggregate, named `{Aggregate}Controller` in `presentation/controllers/`.
- Inject **use cases only** â€” never repositories or Prisma directly.
- Map domain entities to API types via `presentation/mappers/`, not inline in controllers.
- Let `HttpExceptionFilter` + `mapDomainErrorToHttpStatus` translate domain errors to HTTP.

### Use Cases

- One class per operation: `CreatePlayerUseCase`, `ListPlayersUseCase`.
- Single public method: `execute(command | query)`.
- Accept plain command/query objects from `application/commands/` or `application/queries/`.
- Throw domain errors (`PlayerNotFoundError`), never `HttpException`.

### Domain Errors

- Extend `DomainError` with a `readonly code` string.
- Follow naming conventions for HTTP mapping:
  - `*_NOT_FOUND` â†’ 404
  - `INVALID_*` â†’ 400
  - `CONFLICT_*` â†’ 409
  - default â†’ 422

### Repository Ports

- Define interface + injection token in `domain/repositories/`.
- Token pattern: `export const PLAYER_REPOSITORY = Symbol('PLAYER_REPOSITORY');`
- Implement in `infrastructure/persistence/prisma-{entity}.repository.ts`.

### Module Wiring

- `{module}.module.ts` is the **only** file that binds infrastructure to domain ports.
- Export use cases and repository tokens if other modules need them.
- Register module in `app.module.ts`.

### Logging & Config

- Use `LoggerService` from `common/logging/` â€” not `console.log`.
- Environment variables via `@nestjs/config`; never hardcode secrets or connection strings.

## Forbidden Patterns

- `@Injectable()` on use case classes.
- Injecting `PrismaService` into controllers or use cases.
- Returning Prisma models from use cases or controllers.
- Catching domain errors in controllers and re-mapping manually.
- `any` types in domain or application layers.
- Skipping DTO validation with raw `@Body() body: Record<string, unknown>`.
- Global state or singletons for request-scoped data.

## Good Examples

```typescript
// presentation/controllers/players.controller.ts
@Controller('players')
export class PlayersController {
  constructor(private readonly createPlayerUseCase: CreatePlayerUseCase) {}

  @Post()
  @HttpCode(HttpStatus.CREATED)
  async create(@Body() dto: CreatePlayerDto): Promise<ApiResponse<PlayerSummary>> {
    const player = await this.createPlayerUseCase.execute({
      name: dto.name,
      position: dto.position,
      overallRating: dto.overallRating,
    });
    return { data: toPlayerSummary(player) };
  }
}
```

```typescript
// domain/repositories/player.repository.ts
export interface PlayerRepository {
  findById(id: PlayerId): Promise<Player | null>;
  findAll(): Promise<readonly Player[]>;
  save(player: Player): Promise<void>;
}

export const PLAYER_REPOSITORY = Symbol('PLAYER_REPOSITORY');
```

```typescript
// application/use-cases/get-player-by-id.use-case.ts
export class GetPlayerByIdUseCase {
  constructor(private readonly playerRepository: PlayerRepository) {}

  async execute(query: GetPlayerByIdQuery): Promise<Player> {
    const id = PlayerId.create(query.playerId);
    const player = await this.playerRepository.findById(id);
    if (player === null) {
      throw new PlayerNotFoundError(query.playerId);
    }
    return player;
  }
}
```

## Bad Examples

```typescript
// BAD: controller talks to Prisma
@Controller('players')
export class PlayersController {
  constructor(private readonly prisma: PrismaService) {}

  @Get(':id')
  async findOne(@Param('id') id: string) {
    return this.prisma.player.findUnique({ where: { id } });
  }
}
```

```typescript
// BAD: use case with NestJS decorator
@Injectable()
export class CreatePlayerUseCase {
  constructor(@Inject(PLAYER_REPOSITORY) private repo: PlayerRepository) {}
}
```

```typescript
// BAD: HTTP exception in use case
async execute(query: GetPlayerByIdQuery): Promise<Player> {
  const player = await this.playerRepository.findById(id);
  if (!player) throw new NotFoundException('Player not found');
  return player;
}
```

## Checklist

- [ ] Controller delegates to use cases only
- [ ] DTOs validated with class-validator decorators
- [ ] Response wrapped in `{ data }` with shared-types shapes
- [ ] Domain errors used instead of HTTP exceptions in use cases
- [ ] Repository port defined in domain, implemented in infrastructure
- [ ] Use case wired with `provideUseCase()` and symbol token
- [ ] No Prisma or NestJS imports in domain/application layers
